snippet.textDisplay:
I’m in Australia and I believe that all Western countries are telling civilians not to wear masks as the health department is in need of them and if the public hoards them, they will be out.

Having said that, I don’t think they should misinform the public saying it doesn’t do anything.

Results in South Korea show that approximately 80% is physical contact and bodily fluid and 20% is airborne.

It does have protective barrier against airborne viruses to an extent and it is beneficial to have at least something.

If the masks didn’t do anything why would the doctors and medical staff wear exposure prone protective gear. Might as well just see them bare faced if they claim that it doesn’t do anything.

Unfortunately some people see this as means of making money for themselves in exchange of others lives and their quality of life.

I have food at my place as I was prepared way back when it first started in Wuhan as I follow politics closely in Korea and around the world.

I believe people should get ready for lockdowns for many months to come but not excessively hoard things that they don’t need.

Being in health profession, I will most likely be at a higher risk of being infected but all the best for everyone.
